01:00:00.160 --> 01:00:06.720
An academic transcript is a history of grades&nbsp;
in various courses. You could say it's karma.&nbsp;

01:00:06.720 --> 01:00:10.080
You make choices. You make&nbsp;
choices to pay attention,&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:00:10.080 --> 01:00:14.880
not to pay attention, to apply yourself,
not to apply yourself. You make choices.&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:00:14.880 --> 01:00:20.000
The cumulative effect of all those choices
is your transcript at the end of college.&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:00:21.600 --> 01:00:24.480
It's like that in life. We're&nbsp;
making choices constantly.&nbsp;

01:00:24.480 --> 01:00:32.160
There's nothing magical or infamous about karma.&nbsp;
It's just reminding us that not only does the&nbsp;

01:00:32.160 --> 01:00:39.600
physical world move according to cause and effect,&nbsp;
but our psychological world also moves according&nbsp;

01:00:39.600 --> 01:00:47.600
to cause and effect, and our spiritual world does&nbsp;
too, except that there is a depth in the spiritual&nbsp;

01:00:47.600 --> 01:00:51.440
level. There may be also in&nbsp;
the quantum level as well,&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:00:51.440 --> 01:00:57.920
but there is a depth in the physical level
which you discover deep inside your center&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:00:57.920 --> 01:01:02.640
that is not part of cause and&nbsp;
effect. It's outside of cause&nbsp;

01:01:02.640 --> 01:01:11.200
and effect. The spiritual traditions make a great&nbsp;
deal of emphasis of reducing the turbulence of&nbsp;

01:01:11.200 --> 01:01:19.040
karma, cause and effect, until one can actually&nbsp;
experience the aspect of your own being which is&nbsp;

01:01:19.040 --> 01:01:27.600
free of cause and effect. When they describe&nbsp;
one's essential nature, one's divine nature,&nbsp;

01:01:27.600 --> 01:01:34.160
it never begins, it never ends. It doesn't&nbsp;
have a beginning and end. It's always present.&nbsp;

01:01:34.160 --> 01:01:40.400
It's always stable. Karma has beginning and end.&nbsp;
It runs around, does all sorts, like a playground,&nbsp;

01:01:40.400 --> 01:01:45.040
but underneath there is this reality&nbsp;
which has neither beginning nor end.&nbsp;

01:01:45.840 --> 01:01:53.840
Spiritual practice is about living more of your&nbsp;
life from that reality rather than living your&nbsp;

01:01:53.840 --> 01:02:02.640
life from that turbulence, cause and effect. What&nbsp;
role do historical traumas and collective traumas&nbsp;

01:02:02.640 --> 01:02:07.920
play in what we're experiencing here on earth? Of&nbsp;
course, I know you mentioned earlier there's a lot&nbsp;

01:02:07.920 --> 01:02:17.280
of pleasant attributes we bring with us as well.&nbsp;
All the virtues of history are poured into us,&nbsp;

01:02:17.280 --> 01:02:24.400
that surround us, as well as all the burdens of&nbsp;
bad choices of history, all the sins of history.&nbsp;

01:02:24.400 --> 01:02:31.600
We seem to be in a very intense time now. We're&nbsp;
coming into a critical time in human history.&nbsp;

01:02:31.600 --> 01:02:39.440
We've never been here before. We've had
pieces of continents in danger, but now we&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:02:39.440 --> 01:02:47.120
have an entire planet that's in danger of becoming
unable to sustain our population. And we're doing&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:02:47.120 --> 01:02:52.320
it. It's human-made. We're making the choices.
We're causing the problem. Nature is not causing&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:02:52.320 --> 01:03:00.320
the problem. We are causing the problem.
And so, we seem to be in a time of increasing&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:03:00.320 --> 01:03:07.120
turbulence, disruption, chaos. We're dealing
with a lot of social uncertainty and social&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:03:07.120 --> 01:03:14.400
divisiveness because many people are not clear
how to face the challenges that were coming into&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:03:14.400 --> 01:03:19.360
us as species. We know that global climate change
is going to have enormous impact.&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:03:19.360 --> 01:03:24.880
We're going to be losing many,&nbsp;
many, many lives in the near future,&nbsp;

01:03:24.880 --> 01:03:36.160
in the future. And this leads to uncertainty and&nbsp;
a lot of turbulence. And if we look at this same&nbsp;

01:03:36.160 --> 01:03:44.400
situation from within a deep spiritual perspective&nbsp;
and we ask, what is causing this inner turbulence?&nbsp;

01:03:44.400 --> 01:03:50.560
Well, in some ways, I look towards&nbsp;
the lives of individual mystics.&nbsp;

01:03:50.560 --> 01:03:57.280
When we look at the life of an individual&nbsp;
mystic, this is well documented and testified&nbsp;

01:03:57.280 --> 01:04:02.080
that before the breakthrough of enlightenment,&nbsp;
before the breakthrough of the universal&nbsp;

01:04:02.080 --> 01:04:07.760
one heart, we go through the dark night of&nbsp;
the soul. We go through a period of deep,&nbsp;

01:04:07.760 --> 01:04:13.760
deep, intense personal cleansing. And another&nbsp;
way of thinking about this from a reincarnational&nbsp;

01:04:13.760 --> 01:04:20.000
perspective is that we're cleaning the basement.&nbsp;
All the things inside of us which are incompatible&nbsp;

01:04:20.000 --> 01:04:26.000
with enlightenment, all the history which has&nbsp;
led us to have convictions and urges and whatnot,&nbsp;

01:04:26.000 --> 01:04:32.800
which are incompatible with universal love,&nbsp;
are being forced out of the system. And in your&nbsp;

01:04:32.800 --> 01:04:40.800
meditation, the spiritual practitioners can&nbsp;
experience that. They experience upheavals&nbsp;

01:04:40.800 --> 01:04:46.560
coming up from within them. Sometimes they're&nbsp;
crying on the meditation cushion. Sometimes&nbsp;

01:04:46.560 --> 01:04:52.800
they're feeling unspeakable rage, but the advice&nbsp;
is always the same. Keep centered, let it flow&nbsp;

01:04:52.800 --> 01:04:59.840
through you. It will pass. It will move through&nbsp;
you. If we kind of think of the entire species&nbsp;

01:04:59.840 --> 01:05:06.320
as a single meditating being, I think something&nbsp;
like this is happening. I personally think we&nbsp;

01:05:06.320 --> 01:05:16.880
are entering into a profoundly important, very&nbsp;
positive turning point in human evolution,&nbsp;

01:05:16.880 --> 01:05:20.880
which will take us into a&nbsp;
higher level of psycho-spiritual&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:05:20.880 --> 01:05:27.920
functioning at an across-the-board
platform. For us to actualize this, for&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:05:27.920 --> 01:05:34.800
us to realize this, we have to clear ourselves of
everything which is keeping us from experiencing&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:05:34.800 --> 01:05:40.400
this state right here, right now, today.
And the things which are keeping us from&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:05:40.400 --> 01:05:46.240
experiencing this is all our collective
karma and collective history and all our cultural&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:05:46.240 --> 01:05:52.000
institutions and the history that each of us
carry individually and we all carry collectively&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:05:52.000 --> 01:05:59.200
together. So I think that we are actually
experiencing a time of tremendous purification.&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:06:02.000 --> 01:06:07.760
It's kind of like you have to expose the shadow
before you can heal the shadow. And we&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:06:07.760 --> 01:06:12.240
are certainly exposing the&nbsp;
shadow of humanity right now&nbsp;

01:06:12.240 --> 01:06:20.160
in many of the very destructive and self-absorbed&nbsp;
and injurious policies or practices that are&nbsp;

01:06:20.160 --> 01:06:27.440
arising in our midst. I think of this as kind of a&nbsp;
collective purification, which is part and parcel&nbsp;

01:06:27.440 --> 01:06:34.720
of leading into a spiritual awakening,&nbsp;
the deep and profound spiritual awakening.&nbsp;

01:06:34.720 --> 01:06:44.080
Yes, Carl Jung and the shadow, focusing&nbsp;
on our own individual shadow selves or&nbsp;

01:06:44.080 --> 01:06:54.800
letting ourselves maybe heal from what ails us.&nbsp;
What would you suggest people consider doing&nbsp;

01:06:54.800 --> 01:07:04.640
as far as do they primarily focus on their own&nbsp;
selves and or assisting the collective? I mean,&nbsp;

01:07:04.640 --> 01:07:09.280
I understand what you're saying that as we focus&nbsp;
on ourselves, we're part of the collective.&nbsp;

01:07:09.280 --> 01:07:17.280
It's a both-hand situation, isn't it? Because&nbsp;
while an enlightened individual in a monastery,&nbsp;

01:07:17.280 --> 01:07:23.120
in a mountain with no contact in the world&nbsp;
may have an uplifting effect on the whole,&nbsp;

01:07:24.080 --> 01:07:31.920
that person has that reality. Most of us live&nbsp;
embodied in the world, and we would like to do&nbsp;

