other spiritual practices that time, but I was&nbsp;
always working as an academic. I was working hard&nbsp;

01:08:29.200 --> 01:08:37.200
at an open enrollment university and trying to&nbsp;
raise that corner. That was my garden. That was&nbsp;

01:08:37.200 --> 01:08:41.280
where I worked and where I was trying to make&nbsp;
things better. And all of my colleagues, they&nbsp;

01:08:41.280 --> 01:08:46.400
had their gardens. They were working to make&nbsp;
things better in the world. And so I don't think&nbsp;

01:08:46.400 --> 01:08:52.720
it's an either or. I think some people&nbsp;
are drawn more to this incarnation,&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:08:52.720 --> 01:08:55.040
to an individual interior&nbsp;

01:08:55.040 --> 01:09:01.920
project. Other people are drawn&nbsp;
more to an exterior social project.&nbsp;

01:09:01.920 --> 01:09:05.280
There's not a right or wrong&nbsp;
here. I think it's both-and.&nbsp;

01:09:05.280 --> 01:09:09.680
What would you like to say to someone&nbsp;
who may be listening, thinking,&nbsp;

01:09:09.680 --> 01:09:15.840
well, I'm doing my part, but that person or&nbsp;
that group or that institution or that country&nbsp;

01:09:15.840 --> 01:09:20.800
is really messing things&nbsp;
up and they're the problem?&nbsp;

01:09:20.800 --> 01:09:26.160
Yeah. And they may be. And there are&nbsp;
certainly people, other players in the world,&nbsp;

01:09:26.160 --> 01:09:32.160
besides ourselves, and they're doing bad things&nbsp;
in the world. Any right-thinking person would&nbsp;

