reincarnational worldview and understanding the&nbsp;
deep, deep forces that guide people's lives and&nbsp;

01:09:57.680 --> 01:10:06.720
set up circumstances is it's an absolute waste of&nbsp;
time to be envious of someone else's good fortune.&nbsp;

01:10:06.720 --> 01:10:13.360
You should never judge someone else's bad&nbsp;
fortune. We don't know what got them there.&nbsp;

01:10:13.360 --> 01:10:19.040
We don't know whether this is a saint or a sinner.&nbsp;
It could be a sinner inheriting bad karma or it&nbsp;

01:10:19.040 --> 01:10:26.240
could be a saint who's taken on somebody else's&nbsp;
bad karma. We don't know. Best to take care of&nbsp;

01:10:26.240 --> 01:10:32.800
your own shop. Best to do the very, very best&nbsp;
you can with the circumstances in which you find&nbsp;

01:10:32.800 --> 01:10:35.760
yourselves in because there's&nbsp;
meaning and intention in those&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:10:35.760 --> 01:10:42.160
circumstances. Engage that part of the
outside world which is yours to engage.&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:10:43.360 --> 01:10:46.800
A lot of it is recognizing&nbsp;
that people are at different&nbsp;

01:10:46.800 --> 01:10:56.560
stages of their life, their soul's life, and we&nbsp;
have to stand the ground that we need to stand&nbsp;

01:10:56.560 --> 01:11:01.280
but most of our judgments aren't about standing&nbsp;
ground. It's just being judgmental in the way&nbsp;

01:11:01.280 --> 01:11:06.800
that creates more barriers that only have to&nbsp;
be taken down later. Judgments are barriers.&nbsp;

01:11:08.480 --> 01:11:15.920
There's a way in which we can draw conclusions&nbsp;
but without living within the harsh boundaries&nbsp;

01:11:15.920 --> 01:11:25.360
of judgments. Do you feel we're going&nbsp;
through a collective near-death experience&nbsp;

01:11:25.360 --> 01:11:31.360
even though we don't really die since&nbsp;
our consciousness seems to continue?&nbsp;

01:11:31.360 --> 01:11:38.240
Yeah. I think we are going through something like&nbsp;
that. What happens when people have a near fatal&nbsp;

01:11:38.240 --> 01:11:47.760
accident and we know that when their mind speeds&nbsp;
up, they become able to do physical things that&nbsp;

01:11:47.760 --> 01:11:53.280
they would never have dreamed that they could do.&nbsp;
If they're falling off a mountain, they can take&nbsp;

01:11:53.280 --> 01:12:00.800
action along the way. The mind speeds up and often&nbsp;
the heart opens, the mind opens. One enters into&nbsp;

01:12:00.800 --> 01:12:11.120
transcendent spaces under the pressure of almost&nbsp;
dying. Now, it's not being alarmist to say that&nbsp;

01:12:11.120 --> 01:12:18.240
we are going into a near extinction event on&nbsp;
this planet. The crises which have only now just&nbsp;

01:12:18.240 --> 01:12:23.600
beginning to start are going to be getting worse&nbsp;
and everything we're doing in this country,&nbsp;

01:12:23.600 --> 01:12:29.600
I'm afraid, politically is going to make that&nbsp;
crisis, that confrontation with the planet's&nbsp;

01:12:29.600 --> 01:12:40.000
limits even harder and more severe. Clearly, we're&nbsp;
going into very, very difficult and challenging&nbsp;

01:12:40.000 --> 01:12:47.840
times and there are some very smart people, good&nbsp;
clear-thinking people who basically have concluded&nbsp;

01:12:47.840 --> 01:12:53.600
that's it. Humanity is toast. We're living&nbsp;
on extended time. There's no reversing this&nbsp;

01:12:53.600 --> 01:12:59.040
process. We're going to go extinct. We're&nbsp;
going to die. We just don't know it yet.&nbsp;

01:12:59.040 --> 01:13:04.240
But if you look at the statistics, you look&nbsp;
at the information, you look at the patterns,&nbsp;

01:13:04.240 --> 01:13:11.280
we're going extinct. I personally don't think&nbsp;
we are going extinct, but I don't believe that&nbsp;

01:13:11.280 --> 01:13:16.800
like on rational calculus grounds. I believe it&nbsp;
because of my spiritual experiences that we do&nbsp;

01:13:16.800 --> 01:13:23.680
make it through this crisis. But it clearly is&nbsp;
going to be a planet-changing crisis. It's going&nbsp;

01:13:23.680 --> 01:13:29.360
to be a civilization-changing crisis. It's going&nbsp;
to be a near-death experience of our culture,&nbsp;

01:13:29.360 --> 01:13:35.600
of our life on this planet. And we might learn&nbsp;
something about what might happen during it&nbsp;

01:13:35.600 --> 01:13:41.040
if we study people, individuals who have had&nbsp;
near-death experiences. So I think we are,&nbsp;

01:13:41.040 --> 01:13:47.120
I think things are speeding up. I think things&nbsp;
are becoming dire. I think there are fewer and&nbsp;

01:13:47.120 --> 01:13:54.080
fewer innocent decisions. Every decision has&nbsp;
infinite ramifications. I think we're coming&nbsp;

01:13:54.080 --> 01:14:01.520
into a make or break point. We're coming into&nbsp;
a point of grow up or die. And the threat of&nbsp;

01:14:01.520 --> 01:14:05.440
extinction is a tremendous&nbsp;
evolutionary accelerator.&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:14:05.440 --> 01:14:11.360
And I think we're coming into a time where we're
beginning to realize that if we don't change our&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:14:11.360 --> 01:14:20.560
practices, we're going to lose our life on this
planet. And that core deep down inside, this&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:14:20.560 --> 01:14:27.120
transformation that's required is not simply
a transformation of politics or economics&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:14:27.120 --> 01:14:34.400
or industrial production or agricultural.
It's not that primarily. It is fundamentally&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:14:34.400 --> 01:14:41.040
a crisis of consciousness. It is the structure
of human consciousness that has gotten us&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:14:41.040 --> 01:14:48.880
into this mess. It's the limitations of ego,
the loneliness, the self-centeredness of our&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:14:48.880 --> 01:14:55.360
so-called cut-off ego that has led us into
these dead-end scenarios of just consuming&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:14:55.360 --> 01:15:03.120
more and more and more, but not experience any
satisfaction that really gives us any deep, true&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:15:03.120 --> 01:15:09.760
psychospiritual nourishment. We either make it
through this crisis or we go extinct.&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:15:09.760 --> 01:15:13.680
I personally, because that's&nbsp;
the visions I've been given,&nbsp;

01:15:13.680 --> 01:15:18.720
I think we make it through. My concern is&nbsp;
how many of our children and grandchildren&nbsp;

01:15:18.720 --> 01:15:25.760
and great-grandchildren are going to die before&nbsp;
we make it through. That's my major concern.&nbsp;

01:15:25.760 --> 01:15:34.160
There may be those listening, thinking,&nbsp;
well, if there is this oceanic&nbsp;

01:15:34.160 --> 01:15:39.360
wave of love and oneness, why does&nbsp;
it have to get so bad or hard?&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:15:39.360 --> 01:15:43.840
Why do we have to get to this point?
Why do we have to suffer so much? Why does&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:15:43.840 --> 01:15:53.840
there have to be pain and suffering and people
being treated poorly and dying a bodily death&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:15:53.840 --> 01:16:00.400
when maybe they didn't otherwise have to?
Yeah. Boy, that's a hard question. You're&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:16:00.400 --> 01:16:05.840
asking hard questions today.
Because you're basically asking&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:16:05.840 --> 01:16:10.240
the question, why is there suffering?
If there is intelligence and wisdom&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:16:10.240 --> 01:16:15.760
and love as a starting point of&nbsp;
creation, why is it so damn hard?&nbsp;

01:16:15.760 --> 01:16:22.080
Why do we suffer so much? Why didn't somebody give&nbsp;
us an instruction manual to help us do better?&nbsp;

01:16:22.080 --> 01:16:29.440
Why is it so hard? We get angry at the divine&nbsp;
intelligence and we think we could do it better.&nbsp;

01:16:29.440 --> 01:16:33.200
If I were doing this universe, I could design&nbsp;
a better universe. There wouldn't be as much&nbsp;

01:16:33.200 --> 01:16:39.120
suffering. We'd do it differently.&nbsp;
But all of that assumes that we know&nbsp;

01:16:39.120 --> 01:16:47.040
what is being built. We judge from the context of&nbsp;
our own historical position and we make judgments&nbsp;

01:16:47.040 --> 01:16:53.520
about what a good humanity would look like or what&nbsp;
a spiritually realized humanity would look like&nbsp;

01:16:53.520 --> 01:16:59.120
or just what a peaceful humanity would look&nbsp;
like. And this is how we could build toward that.&nbsp;

01:16:59.120 --> 01:17:03.520
But maybe we're not building toward&nbsp;
that. Maybe we're building through that.&nbsp;

01:17:05.360 --> 01:17:10.880
Clearly, the creative intelligence thinks on a&nbsp;
huge landscape. When you really just meditate&nbsp;

01:17:10.880 --> 01:17:18.000
on what astrophysics has taught us and astronomy&nbsp;
has taught us, the landscape of creation is vast&nbsp;

01:17:18.000 --> 01:17:26.000
and magnificent. So we have to genuinely ask&nbsp;
ourselves, okay, what is this intelligence&nbsp;

01:17:26.000 --> 01:17:32.720
creating in this species? What is the project?&nbsp;
Where are we going? What might we become?&nbsp;

01:17:33.280 --> 01:17:42.720
And if we expand in even lightly 100,000&nbsp;
years, which is a second in cosmic time,&nbsp;

01:17:42.720 --> 01:17:48.720
even if we imagine what would be the best&nbsp;
that we could become in 100,000 years,&nbsp;

01:17:48.720 --> 01:17:57.840
we might begin to understand where suffering&nbsp;
fits into this larger agenda, which is larger&nbsp;

01:17:57.840 --> 01:18:02.560
than most of our agenda. Most of us would think&nbsp;
if we could just get comfortable and be a happy&nbsp;

01:18:02.560 --> 01:18:08.800
human being as we are and live, eat, and die,&nbsp;
we'd be okay. But maybe that's not the agenda&nbsp;

01:18:08.800 --> 01:18:15.920
of existence at all, of the creative intelligence.&nbsp;
And I don't mean to treat people suffering&nbsp;

01:18:15.920 --> 01:18:25.120
cavalierly. I truly do not mean so. I mean, it's&nbsp;
all great respect to those who suffer, honestly.&nbsp;

01:18:25.120 --> 01:18:31.840
But suffering in some ways in our time is like&nbsp;
when we're building a house and we have the walls&nbsp;

01:18:31.840 --> 01:18:37.520
up, the stud walls up, and we have the trusses up&nbsp;
that we haven't put on the roof. And if it rains,&nbsp;

01:18:37.520 --> 01:18:40.720
rain comes in. It's because&nbsp;
the house is unfinished.&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:18:40.720 --> 01:18:44.560
It's not because there's any structural
design flaw in the house. The house is just&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:18:44.560 --> 01:18:52.880
not finished. Humanity is an unfinished species.
Sri Aurobindo made a large point of this. He&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:18:52.880 --> 01:18:57.360
talked about how humanity&nbsp;
is a transitional species.&nbsp;

01:18:57.360 --> 01:19:03.360
We are transitioning from what we were 100,000&nbsp;
years ago into what we are in the process of&nbsp;

01:19:03.360 --> 01:19:10.640
becoming deep. We are not the end of the project.&nbsp;
We are just in the middle of the project.&nbsp;

01:19:10.640 --> 01:19:18.400
In that context, if we take disease, for&nbsp;
example, we are only at the early stages&nbsp;

01:19:18.400 --> 01:19:25.760
of developing our consciousness so clearly and&nbsp;
strongly that we can heal diseases in our body&nbsp;

